Author-Name:    Dixit, Avinash
Title:   Irreversible Investment with Price Ceilings. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 541-57
Issue: 3
Volume: 99
Year: 1991
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  A model of irreversible investment in a competitive industry under demand
 uncertainty is developed. In the absence of restrictions, investment by
 itself will keep the price from rising above a natural ceiling that
 exceeds the long-run average cost by an option value factor. When a lower
 ceiling is imposed, investment is triggered only by the observation of an
 even higher "shadow" price. As the imposed ceiling is reduced to the
 long-run average cost, this shadow price goes to infinity and investment
 ceases completely. Because investment is depressed, a tighter price
 ceiling generally leads to a higher long-run average price.  Copyright 1991 by University of Chicago Press.
